[The serotype of the enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ is not stated. The prototypic strain is O157:H7. It is possible that this outbreak and the one in Ohio may have the same source. ProMED awaits more information, but a presumptive vehicle for some, if not most, of the cases ought to be found using food surveys or history of recent visits to petting zoos or other high-risk places.

Michigan and Ohio are adjacent states in the upper midwestern area of the USA. - Mod.LL

